20major%20city.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223155%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seattle%20Skyline%20with%20Mount%20Rainier%20in%20the%20background%20at%20sunset%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6830de81c6ad288d1481d7a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222366%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMount%20Rainier%20is%20seen%20from%20Seattle.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20K%20Collins%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20hotel's%20rooftop%20deck%2C%20a%20local%20pointed%20to%20a%20mountain%20in%20the%20distance%20and%20told%20me%20it%20was%20an%20active%20volcano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20hardly%20see%20the%20volcano%20through%20the%20haze%2C%20but%20they%20told%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeadly-volcanoes-that-could-erupt-soon-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMount%20Rainier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20last%20erupted%20in%201894%2C%20was%20more%20visible%20on%20clear%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20shocked%20to%20learn%20that%20this%20city%2C%20home%20to%20nearly%20800%2C000%20people%2C%20is%20so%20close%20to%20what%20could%20be%20a%20natural%20disaster.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattle.gov%2Fdocuments%2FDepartments%2FEmergency%2FPlansOEM%2FSHIVA%2F2014-04-23_VolcanoHazards.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Seattle%20Office%20of%20Emergency%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20city%20is%20a%20safe%20distance%20away%20from%20a%20potential%20blast's%20flow%2C%20but%20water%20and%20power%20resources%20could%20be%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMy%20trip%20to%20Seattle%20was%20everything%20I%20hoped%20it%20would%20be%20and%20more.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20stands%20on%20a%20rooftop%20deck%20in%20front%20of%20city%20buildings%20with%20a%20Ferris%20wheel%20on%20the%20right%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683db241c6ad288d14824dd3%3Fform