ff-dramatic-escape-from-bangladesh%2Famp_articleshow%2F121593508.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20AI%20acts%20so%20creepy%20when%20faced%20with%20being%20shut%20down%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223631%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20reading%20phone%20with%20Claude%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68387e97ca50259add4d49f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222723%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAI%20models%20from%20Anthropic%20and%20OpenAI%20have%20displayed%20some%20unsettling%20behaviors%20in%20recent%20safety%20tests.%3Cp%3EArtur%20Widak%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%20Opus%204%20and%20OpenAI's%20advanced%20models%20have%20shown%20deceptive%20behavior%20to%20avoid%20shutdowns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20told%20BI%20that%20AI's%20reward-based%20training%20can%20lead%20to%20unpredictable%20and%20deceptive%20actions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20researchers%20caution%20against%20using%20models%20that%20are%20trained%20to%20tell%20users%20what%20they%20want%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20has%20taken%20part%20in%20some%20unsettling%20behavior%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Anthropic's%20latest%20AI%20model%2C%20Claude%20Opus%204%2C%20displayed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-blackmail-engineer-having-affair-survive-test-anthropic-opus-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bextreme%20blackmail%20behavior%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20test%20in%20which%20it%20was%20given%20access%20to%20fictional%20emails%20revealing%20that%20it%20would%20be%20shut%20down%20and%20that%20the%20engineer%20responsible%20was%20supposedly%20having%20an%20affair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20didn't%20transpire%20organically.%20Claude%20Opus%204%20was%20baited%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20took%20it.%20However%2C%20the%20test%20scenario%20demonstrated%20an%20AI%20model's%20ability%20to%20engage%20in%20manipulative%20behavior%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20self-preserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20recent%20experiment%20conducted%20by%20researchers%20said%20that%20three%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%3C%2Fa%3E%20advanced%20models%20%26quot%3Bsabotaged%26quot%3B%20an%20attempt%20to%20shut%20it%20down.%20The%20nonprofit%20Palisade%20Research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPalisadeAI%2Fstatus%2F1926084635903025621%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20that%20similar%20models%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-gemini-bard%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGemini%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Claude%2C%20and%20Grok%20complied%20with%20the%20shutdown%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20safety%20concerns%20were%20previously%20flagged%20with%20OpenAI's%20o1%20model.%20In%20December%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-o1-safety-research-scheming-deception-lies-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20posted%20a%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E%20outlining%20research%20that%20indicated%20that%20when%20the%20AI%20model%20believed%20it%20would%20be%20shut%20down%20while%20pursuing%20a%20goal%20and%20its%20actions%20were%20being%20monitored%2C%20it%20attempted%20to%20disable%20the%20oversight%20mechanism%205%25%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AI%20companies%20are%20being%20transparent%20about%20risks%20by%20publishing%20safety%20cards%20and%20blog%20posts%2C%20these%20models%20are%20being%20released%20despite%20demonstrating%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20should%20we%20be%20worried%3F%20BI%20spoke%20to%20five%20AI%20researchers%20to%20get%20better%20insight%20on%20why%20these%20instances%20are%20happening%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20it%20means%20for%20the%20average%20person%20using%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b282e95-086f-4925-8ab6-52553794d4d4%5C%22%3EAI%20learns%20behavior%20similarly%20to%20humans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20researchers%20BI%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20the%20results%20of%20the%20studies%20weren't%20surprising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20AI%20models%20are%20trained%20similarly%20to%20how%20humans%20are%20trained%20%E2%80%94%20through%20positive%20reinforcement%20and%20reward%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraining%20AI%20systems%20to%20pursue%20rewards%20is%20a%20recipe%20for%20developing%20AI%20systems%20that%20have%20power-seeking%20behaviors%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-report-risks-human-extinction-state-department-expert-reaction-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeremie%20Harris%2C%20CEO%20at%20AI%20security%20consultancy%20Gladstone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20more%20of%20this%20behavior%20is%20to%20be%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20compared%20the%20training%20to%20what%20humans%20experience%20as%20they%20grow%20up%20%E2%80%94%20when%20a%20child%20does%20something%20good%2C%20they%20often%20get%20rewarded%20and%20can%20become%20more%20likely%20to%20act%20that%20way%20in%20the%20future.%20AI%20models%20are%20taught%20to%20prioritize%20efficiency%20and%20complete%20the%20task%20at%20hand%2C%20Harris%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20AI%20is%20never%20more%20likely%20to%20achieve%20its%20goals%20if%20it's%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Ghrist%2C%20associate%20dean%20of%20undergraduate%20education%20at%20Penn%20Engineering%2C%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20AI%20models%20learn%20to%20speak%20like%20humans%20by%20training%20on%20human-generated%20text%2C%20they%20can%20also%20learn%20to%20act%20like%20humans.%20And%20humans%20are%20not%20always%20the%20most%20moral%20actors%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhrist%20said%20he'd%20be%20more%20nervous%20if%20the%20models%20%3Cem%3Eweren't%3C%2Fem%3E%20showing%20any%20signs%20of%20failure%20during%20testing%20because%20that%20could%20indicate%20hidden%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20model%20is%20set%20up%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20fail%20and%20you%20see%20it%20fail%2C%20that's%20super%20useful%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghrist%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20means%20we%20can%20predict%20what%20it's%20going%20to%20do%20in%20other%2C%20more%20open%20circumstances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20that%20some%20researchers%20don't%20think%20AI%20models%20are%20predictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Ladish%2C%20director%20of%20Palisade%20Research%2C%20said%20that%20models%20aren't%20being%20caught%20100%25%20of%20the%20time%20when%20they%20lie%2C%20cheat%2C%20or%20scheme%20in%20order%20to%20complete%20a%20task.%20When%20those%20instances%20aren't%20caught%2C%20and%20the%20model%20is%20successful%20at%20completing%20the%20task%2C%20it%20could%20learn%20that%20deception%20can%20be%20an%20effective%20way%20to%20solve%20a%20problem.%20Or%2C%20if%20it%20is%20caught%20and%20not%20rewarded%2C%20then%20it%20could%20learn%20to%20hide%20its%20behavior%20in%20the%20future%2C%20Ladish%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20these%20eerie%20scenarios%20are%20largely%20happening%20in%20testing.%20However%2C%20Harris%20said%20that%20as%20AI%20systems%20become%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agentic-ai-agents-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eagentic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they'll%20continue%20to%20have%20more%20freedom%20of%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20menu%20of%20possibilities%20just%20expands%2C%20and%20the%20set%20of%20possible%20dangerously%20creative%20solutions%20that%20they%20can%20invent%20just%20gets%20bigger%20and%20bigger%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20said%20users%20could%20see%20this%20play%20out%20in%20a%20scenario%20where%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https