X%20factors%20like%20tariffs%20and%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20are%20further%20curbing%20some%20employers'%20appetites%20for%20hiring%2C%20and%20you've%20got%20more%20reasons%20to%20treat%20networking%20like%20healthy%20eating%20or%20hitting%20the%20gym%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20something%20you%20only%20do%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNetworking%20is%20more%20about%20farming%20than%20it%20is%20about%20hunting.%20It's%20about%20cultivating%20relationships%20with%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Ivan%20Misner%2C%20founder%20of%20BNI%2C%20a%20business%20networking%20organization%20focused%20on%20referrals%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20he%20said%20he%20encourages%20people%20to%20start%20now%2C%20before%20they're%20unemployed.%20Misner%2C%20who%20for%20decades%20has%20been%20an%20evangelist%20of%20networking%2C%20compares%20the%20act%20of%20building%20relationships%20to%20the%20adage%20about%20the%20best%20time%20to%20plant%20a%20tree%20being%2020%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20second-best%20time%20being%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20those%20employees%20who%20have%20not%20planted%20an%20oak%20tree%2C%20who%20have%20not%20been%20out%20networking%2C%20they%20need%20to%20go%20do%20it%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f34fb76-9c6c-4380-92e3-aad89a43d9a5%5C%22%3EJoining%20the%20'favor%20economy'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20networking%20is%20more%20essential%20than%20ever%20is%20that%20our%20attention%20is%20often%20fractured%20by%20the%20amount%20of%20information%20coming%20at%20us%2C%20Dorie%20Clark%2C%20a%20communication%20coach%20who%20teaches%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20and%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Long%20Game%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20always%20going%20to%20get%20your%20attention%20is%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20people%20that%20you%20care%20about%20and%20want%20to%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20us%2C%20though%2C%20often%20find%20jobs%20not%20through%20our%20close%20contacts%20but%20through%20their%20acquaintances%2C%20Clark%20said.%20What%20can%20play%20out%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20an%20example%20of%20what's%20sometimes%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bfavor%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20will%20help%20someone%20that%20you%20don't%20know%20that%20well%2C%20because%20you%20are%20indirectly%20doing%20a%20favor%20for%20the%20person%20you%20do%20know%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20that%20because%20AI%20threatens%20to%20take%20jobs%20and%20because%20many%20employers%20are%20cautious%20about%20hiring%2C%20some%20old-school%20relationship-building%20is%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that%20is%20going%20to%20get%20you%20to%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line%20when%20jobs%20are%20scarce%20is%20interpersonal%20relationships%20with%20people%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20go%20above%20and%20beyond%20and%20expend%20political%20capital%20to%20help%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20that%20relying%20too%20much%20on%20social%20media%20as%20a%20means%20of%20networking%20can%20be%20dangerous%20because%20it's%20often%20a%20poor%20substitute%20for%20making%20deeper%20connections%20with%20people%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20gives%20you%20the%20illusion%20of%20productive%20networking.%20It%20gives%20you%20the%20illusion%20of%20connection%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Clark%20advises%20workers%20and%20job%20seekers%20to%20look%20for%20more%20%26quot%3Bbespoke%26quot%3B%20ways%20of%20connecting.%20It%20might%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20sending%20someone%20you%20know%20a%20text%20once%20in%20a%20while%20without%20expecting%20a%20response.%20She%20said%20sharing%20something%20that%20reminds%20you%20of%20that%20person%20or%20simply%20saying%20hello%20can%20make%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20you're%20friendly%2C%20you're%20thoughtful%2C%20you're%20relevant%2C%20you're%20not%20seeking%20something%20from%20them%20%E2%80%94%20most%20people%20will%20be%20very%20happy%20to%20hear%20from%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gold%20standard%2C%20however%2C%20remains%20spending%20time%20with%20someone%20IRL%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20don't%20know%20someone%20well%20%E2%80%94%20and%20especially%20when%20there's%20a%20power%20imbalance%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20best%20to%20make%20a%20single%20small%20ask.%20So%2C%20don't%20request%20a%20coffee%20date%2C%20a%20job%20referral%2C%20and%20a%20testimonial%20quote%2C%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20think%20about%20what%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bhighest%20and%20best%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20how%20someone%20might%20help%20you%20and%20what%20feels%20appropriate%20as%20an%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ede19db-dbce-4668-9fbc-7a9114e0b10c%5C%22%3EFinding%20ways%20to%20stand%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENetworking%20is%20also%20important%20because%20as%20piles%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20stack%20up%20for%20an%20open%20job%2C%20sifting%20through%20them%2C%20even%20with%20the%20help%20of%20applicant-tracking%20software%2C%20can%20be%20a%20heavy%20lift%20for%20busy%20managers%2C%20Gorick%20Ng%2C%20a%20Harvard%20University%20career%20advisor%20and%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Unspoken%20Rules%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20often%20stands%20out%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20someone%20walking%20down%20the%20hall%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20niece%20is%20looking%20for%20a%20job.%20Here's%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20Do%20you%20mind%20just%20taking%20a%20closer%20look%3F%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20Ng%20said%2C%20it%20could%20be%20that%20someone%20on%20the%20inside%20of%20an%20organization%20vouches%20for%20a%20former%20colleague%20by%20saying%20to%20the%20hiring%20manager%20that%20a%20candidate%20is%20likeable%20and%20trustworthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20just%20like%20that%2C%20somebody%20else%20who%20you%20do%20not%20know%20just%20got%20that%20leg%20up%20because%20they%20have%20somebody%20else%20behind%20the%20scenes%20pounding%20on%20the%20table%20for%20their%20name%20to%20be%20picked%2C%26quot%3B%20Ng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it's%20so%20important%20for%20job%20seekers%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20heard%2C%20and%20remembered.%20After%20all%2C%20Ng%20said%2C%20hiring%20managers%20aren't%20likely%20to%20hire%20someone%20they%20haven't%20fallen%20in%20love%20with%20as%20a%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20an%20applicant%20that%20is%20nothing%20more%20than%20just%20a%20Word%20document%20that%20you%20may%20not%20even%20look%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20job%20hunt%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-important-new-job-economy-ai-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748943542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6839e4d7c6ad288d14823cdf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-important-new-job-economy-ai-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20want%20to%20find%20a%20new%20gig%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20double%20down%20on%20networking%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-important-new-job-economy-ai-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C